<!-- LLMAction Block Examples -->
<Vertical id="LLMActionDemo" title="LLMAction Block Demo" launchable="true">

  <Markdown id="intro">
## LLM-Powered Feedback Examples

LLMAction sends prompts to an AI model and displays responses in LLMFeedback components.

**Important**: LLMAction must be nested **inside** ActionButton for automatic discovery.
  </Markdown>

  <!-- Basic feedback example -->
  <Vertical id="water_cycle_example">
    <Markdown id="q1">
### Writing Feedback

Write a paragraph explaining the water cycle:
    </Markdown>
    <TextArea id="water_cycle_response" rows="6" placeholder="Describe the water cycle..." />
    <LLMFeedback id="water_feedback" />

    <ActionButton id="water_btn" label="Get Feedback">
      <LLMAction id="water_action" target="water_feedback">
        A student wrote this explanation of the water cycle:
        <Ref id="water_ref" target="water_cycle_response" />
        Provide brief, encouraging feedback on their explanation. Note any key concepts they covered well and any important points they may have missed.
      </LLMAction>
    </ActionButton>
  </Vertical>

  <!-- Multiple input reference -->
  <Vertical id="compare_example">
    <Markdown id="q2">
### Compare and Contrast

Topic A:
    </Markdown>
    <TextArea id="topic_a" rows="3" placeholder="Describe topic A..." />

    <Markdown id="q2b">
Topic B:
    </Markdown>
    <TextArea id="topic_b" rows="3" placeholder="Describe topic B..." />
    <LLMFeedback id="comparison_feedback" />

    <ActionButton id="compare_btn" label="Analyze Comparison">
      <LLMAction id="compare_action" target="comparison_feedback">
        A student described two topics:

        Topic A: <Ref id="topic_a_ref" target="topic_a" />

        Topic B: <Ref id="topic_b_ref" target="topic_b" />

        Help them identify similarities and differences they may have missed.
      </LLMAction>
    </ActionButton>
  </Vertical>

  <Markdown id="note">
### How It Works

The LLMAction contains the prompt text sent to the AI. Use `&lt;Ref id="unique_id" target="component_id" /&gt;` to include values from input components:

```xml
&lt;LLMAction target="feedback"&gt;
  Please review: &lt;Ref id="my_ref" target="text_input" /&gt;
&lt;/LLMAction&gt;
```

The `target` attribute specifies which LLMFeedback component displays the response.
  </Markdown>

</Vertical>
